[2] Cholera - Zambia (Copperbelt)
Date: Thu, 9 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org<
Source: AllAfrica.com and The Times of Zambia [edited]
<http://allafrica.com/stories/200611090749.html>

The news that cholera has broken out in Chiengi where 12 cases have
been recorded and Sinazongwe where 14 victims have been treated by
health authorities is undoubtedly a source of concern.
With the onset of rains, one can only hope that the requisite
measures will be put in place to ensure that the disease is checked
and no lives are unduly lost. In this regard, the measures by the
health authorities to step up monitoring of movements from the DR
Congo where the Chiengi cases are said to have emanated from, are
commendable.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[Chiengi is in the Copperbelt Province which has its northern border
with Congo DR. The province can be seen at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/zambia.pdf>. -
Mod.LL]
