[3] Cholera - Kenya (Coast)
Date: Thu, 9 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: The Standard [edited]
<http://www.eastandard.net/hm_news/news.php?articleid=1143960894>

The Ministry of Health has announced a cholera outbreak in Mombasa.
The Coast Provincial Medical Officer, Dr Anderson Kahindi, attributed
the outbreak to poor sanitation, which he said had been made worse by
rains that have pounded the town recently. The rains washed off water
pipes and blocked drainage systems.
Two unconfirmed deaths were reported in Magongo, Wayani area of
Changamwe constituency and 3 others in Kongowea in Kisauni
constituency.
The outbreak comes barely 2 days after Local Government minister, Mr
Musikari Kombo said Mombasa was far much dirtier than Kisumu, which
collects less revenue.
Over 10 people who sought treatment at the Tudor Health Clinic,
tested positive for cholera, 2 of them being children under 2 years
of age. Thirty people have been admitted and treated at the health
center in the past 4 days.
[Byline: Caroline Mango]
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
