[5] Cholera - Angola (Cunene)
Date: Tue, 7 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=486099>

Five people died of cholera, from the 87 cases registered in the
districts of Kwanhama and Cuvelai, announced Eduardo Haiumba, the
provincial health director in the southern Cunene province, on Tue, 7
Nov 2006.
According to the director, from this number, 13 are still
hospitalised, while 4 have already been discharged.
The first cholera cases in the province were detected at Kahama
district 30 Sep 2006, and 126 cases and 6 deaths have been registered
up to the current period.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Angola showing that Cunene province can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>. Lunda
Sul and Moxico, in the eastern part of the country, are the only 2
provinces without cholera cases. - Mod.LL]
