[6] Cholera - Angola (Huila)
Date: Tue, 7 Nov 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Angola Press [edited]
<http://www.angolapress-angop.ao/noticia-e.asp?ID=486158>

The acting director of the Provincial Department of Public Health and
Control of Endemic Diseases, Felix Januario, announced that 64 new
cases of cholera were detected in the past 24 hours in the districts
of Quipungo and Lubango, by health authorities of the southern Huila
province. According to him, among these cases, 60 were registered in
Lubango, with deaths, and 4 in Quipungo district without claiming any
life.
Since the cholera outbreak in Huila, in April 2006, the district of
Lubango recorded 1424 cases with 88 deaths, whilst Quipungo district,
120 kilometers from the chief town, detected 47 cases with 14
fatalities.
Also from last Apr 2006, Huila province registered 1825 cases of
cholera and 121 deaths caused by the disease that affected, apart
from Lubango and Quipungo, the districts of Quilengues, Cacula and
Matala.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
[A map of Angola showing that Huila province can be found at:
<http://www.un.org/Depts/Cartographic/map/profile/angola.pdf>. Note
that Huila is north and west of Cunene. - Mod.LL]
